title: Uniqueness of projective transformations
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Let $$P(V)$$ and $$P(W)$$ be two $$n$$-dimensional [[projective spaces|Projective space]] and suppose $$A_1,\dots,A_{n+2}\in P(V)$$ and $$B_1,\dots,B_{n+2}\in P(W)$$ are in [[general position|General position (projective space)]]. Then there is a unique [[projective transformation|Projective transformation]] $$\hat f\colon P(V)\to P(W)$$ with $$\hat f(A_i)=B_i$$ for $$i=1,\dots,n+2.$$